metrics_conclusion: (Break) In Case Of has higher complexity than the average song  in terms Chord-Bass Melody.
key_conclusion: (Break) In Case Of has sections analyzed in the following keys: D Major,  and B Minor.  Click on the linked cheat sheets for popular chords, chord progressions, downloadable midi files and more!

metadata.editComments: Changed the V7 chord back to regular V. Also, forgot to mention that the disonant chord in this progression is borrowed from D minor.

Removed the 7th from the Bb7 chord. I don't actually hear that in the song, I just included that because I'd recently learned about that concept in music theory around when I first heard this song. Moved the A7 as well because I don't hear it until the last note of the vocal harmony goes up to a G.
This is also the second post-chorus. I'm not sure if the ii and iii chords should be notated there, but it didn't make sense to me to keep the I chord.
